
[1]judicious

   JUDI'CIOUS, a.

   1. According to sound judgment; wise; prudent; rational; adapted to
   obtain a good end by the best means; used of things. Nothing is more
   important to success in the world than a judicious application of time,
   unless it may be a judicious expenditure of money.

   2. Acting according to sound judgment; possessing sound judgment; wise;
   directed by reason and wisdom; used of persons; as a judicious
   magistrate; a judicious historian.
